    <stitle>DT 466 / DT 570 / HT 570 Service Manual - 2004 Emissions with EGR - Cylinder Head and Valve Train - Removal
        - Measuring Camshaft Lift
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc graphiccount="3">
        <title>Measuring Camshaft Lift</title>
        <figure id="f2650505" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figeg5/EG5221.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"/>
            <caption>Measuring cam lobes with micrometer</caption>
        </figure>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>If a complete engine overhaul is scheduled, camshaft lobe wear can be determined by
                    <hotlnk document="eges2651_SVCPROC1901.xml" xrefid="Svcproc1901">measuring lobes</hotlnk>
                    with a micrometer after the camshaft is removed.
                </para>
                <para>At this stage of disassembly, determine the appropriate stage of camshaft inspection. If this is
                    not a complete engine overhaul, measure camshaft lobe lift now using the following procedure.
                </para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <figure id="f2650506" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figh08/H08063.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Mounting magnetic base dial indicator</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Mount a magnetic base dial indicator onto the cylinder head.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Place dial indicator tip on top of push rod and rotate engine until push rod is at its
                lowest point of travel (base circle), then "zero" indicator.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f2650507" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figh08/H08064.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Recording camshaft lobe reading</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Rotate the crankshaft and bring push rod to its highest point of travel. Record indicator
                reading.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Repeat this procedure for all lobes.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">For
                <hotlnk document="eges2651_SVCPROC0502.xml" xrefid="t2650501" appearance="hottext">specifications on
                    camshaft lobe</hotlnk>.
            </para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
